							'The most common breakpoints in CSS for responsive web design are based on the various device screen sizes. These breakpoints help ensure that the design is optimized for different devices, such as mobile phones, tablets, and desktops. Here are some common breakpointsn 1. Extra small devices (mobile phones): max-width: 575px 2. Small devices (portrait tablets and large phones): min-width: 576px and max-width: 767px 3. Medium devices (landscape tablets and small laptops): min-width: 768px and max-width: 991px 4. Large devices (laptops and desktops): min-width: 992px and max-width: 1199px 5. Extra large devices (large desktops and TVs): min-width: 1200px  Please note that these breakpoints may vary depending on the design requirements or the specific devices being targeted. It is important to test your design across various devices to ensure proper responsiveness.'
