							"The documentation suggests that you can create a Svelte component library using `@sveltejs/package` and then use SvelteKit to showcase or preview the components in your library. Here's a step-by-step guide on how to do thisn 1. First, create a new folder for your library and navigate to it in your terminaln ```bash mkdir my-svelte-library cd my-svelte-library ```  2. Initialize a new package with npmn ```bash npm init ```  3. Install the `@sveltejs/package` templaten ```bash npx degit sveltejs/component-template ```  4. Install the dependenciesn ```bash npm install ```  Now you have a basic setup for your Svelte component library. You can create your components inside the `src` folder.  5. Next, create a new SvelteKit project in a separate folder to showcase your libraryn ```bash npx degit sveltejs/kit sveltekit-showcase cd sveltekit-showcase ```  6. Install the dependenciesn ```bash npm install ```  7. In your `sveltekit-showcase` folder, open `svelte.config.js`, and add the path to your library package in the `kit.vite.resolve.alias` configurationn ```javascript import { resolve } from 'path';  const config = {   kit: {     //  other configurations     vite: {       resolve: {         alias: {           $mylibrary: resolve('./path/to/your/my-svelte-library/src'),         },       },     },   }, };  export default config; ``"
