							'you and i are designing a new design system, based on hindu principles. two key principles are agency and intent, details of which are given below.  for these 2 principles, using the concepts within them, formulate a toolkit for a designer which asks them 10 questions to identify their agency and intent.  The design of the designer, the shaper of all things that get created. Recognizing the importance of Intent in design is core to our system. That we collectively create a world that none of us individually want is, in significant portion, attributable to a problem of intent. More specifically, to how intent is shaped and directed, once it arises and is noticed. When linked to the three _u015baktis- icch_u0101, j_u00f1_u0101na and kriy_u0101- intent is the very basis of our lives. In the modern world, one shaped more and more by design, the intent that becomes of salience is that of the designer. Reality itself is an intent manifest, in its case shaped and directed by Brahman- the ultimate designer. A designer_u2019s personal values and local ontology will impact both the function and the collateral of what they create, so implementing _u1e5bta in design needs to begin at root- the shaping and planning out of intent. Literature and tools of this principle will address the designer_u2019s inner world. This is the world of cintana- self-reflection, svabh_u0101va- disposition, and j_u00f1_u0101na- knowledge. To anchor the four principles, and to articulate the epitome and vision to aspire to, each of them will be captured in a civilizational guiding statement. Aham Brahm_u0101sm - I am Brahman. ie., designers need keep in mind the power and responsibility at their disposal. That in bringing things to life they enact the great creator, Brahman, means deep consideration and deliberation.   In the grammar-philosophy of Bhart_u1e5bhari, one of India_u2019s greatest linguist _u1e5b_u1e63is, the meaning of an utterance is truly comprehended only at the end of a sentence- not before. It bursts in the listener_u2019s mind after the full v_u0101kya, in a flash of insight Bhart_u1e5bhari called spho_u1e6da. Analogously, the impact, utility and deliverance of design is with the complete implementation. Any meaning, aesthetic, harmony or function finds form only after the act of creation is complete, and the designer needs no further intervention on what they have produced. There are sensitivities needed here for method and procedure, and also for conduct and collaboration- since while intent shaping can reside inside a designer_u2019s head, most large-scale creative endeavours require working with others. This is the realm of prakriy_u0101- processes and methods, of upakara_u1e47a- tools or enablers, and of vyavah_u0101ra- outward conduct and behavior. Material we release to help on this principle will be accordingly designed. The first two principles are directed at the designer- at their inner world and their outward action. The next two principles are aimed at the process of design, and at design as the output/creation of a process. ie., in the journey to being a great designer, the proof is in the excellence of execution- in actually manifesting the intent inside.'
