							'To help designers identify their agency and intent, here is a toolkit with 10 questions based on the principles and concepts describedn 1. What is the core intent behind your design? Reflect on the purpose and goal of your creation. 2. How do your personal values and local ontology influence your design decisions? Consider the impact of your own beliefs on your creation. 3. How will your design positively contribute to the world and the lives of its users? Consider the potential benefits of your design. 4. How do you ensure that your design adheres to the principles of _u1e5bta? Reflect on the balance, harmony, and order in your design. 5. How do you practice self-reflection (cintana) and consider your own disposition (svabh_u0101va) while designing? Reflect on your inner world during the design process. 6. How do you maintain an awareness of the power and responsibility at your disposal (Aham Brahm_u0101sm) during the design process? Consider the impact of your design choices on the world. 7. How do you ensure that your design methods and procedures align with the sensitivities needed for successful implementation? Reflect on the importance of prakriy_u0101 in your design process. 8. What tools or enablers (upakara_u1e47a) do you use to facilitate your design process? Consider how these tools contribute to the successful execution of your intent. 9. How do you manage your outward conduct and behavior (vyavah_u0101ra) when collaborating with others in the design process? Reflect on the importance of teamwork and communication. 10. How do you ensure the excellence of execution in manifesting your intent in the final design? Reflect on the measures you take to achieve a high-quality outcome.  These questions will guide designers in understanding and incorporating the principles of agency and intent in their design process, leading to more thoughtful and impactful creations.'
