							"In Svelte, you can easily track `mousedown` and `mouseup` events just like `click` and `mouseleave`. You simply need to use the `on:EVENTNAME` directive for each event you want to handle. Here's an example of how to track `mousedown` and `mouseup` events in a Svelte componentn ```html <script>   function handleMouseDown(event) {     console.log('Mouse down:', event);   }    function handleMouseUp(event) {     console.log('Mouse up:', event);   } </script>  <style>   div {     width: 100px;     height: 100px;     background-color: lightblue;     display: flex;     justify-content: center;     align-items: center;     cursor: pointer;   } </style>  <div on:mousedown={handleMouseDown} on:mouseup={handleMouseUp}>   Press me </div> ```  In this example, we define two functions `handleMouseDown` and `handleMouseUp` to handle the `mousedown` and `mouseup` events, respectively. Then, we attach these functions to the `div` element using the `on:mousedown` and `on:mouseup` directives. When you press and release the mouse button on the `div`, the respective event handlers will be triggered, and you'll see the console output."
