							"In SvelteKit, you can determine the total height of any page using JavaScript by accessing the `scrollHeight` property of the document's `body` or the `documentElement` (i.e., the `html` tag). Here's a simple Svelte component that shows the total height of the pagen ```html <script>   import { onMount } from 'svelte';    let pageHeight;    onMount(() => {     function updatePageHeight() {       pageHeight = Math.max(         document.body.scrollHeight,         document.documentElement.scrollHeight       );     }      // Update page height on mount     updatePageHeight();      // Update page height when window is resized     window.addEventListener('resize', updatePageHeight);      // Cleanup the event listener     return () => {       window.removeEventListener('resize', updatePageHeight);     };   }); </script>  <style>   /* Add some styles if needed */ </style>  <div>   Total height of the page: {pageHeight}px </div> ```  This Svelte component will display the total height of the page in pixels. The `onMount` function ensures that the height is calculated when the component is mounted and updates it whenever the window is resized. The event listener is removed when the component is unmounted to prevent memory leaks."
