							"To connect the `toggleNav` function in your root layout (`+layout.svelte`) with the button on different pages (`+page.svelte`), you can use Svelte stores to create a shared state that both components can access. Here's how you can do itn 1. Create a new file named `store.js` in your `src` foldern ```javascript // src/store.js import { writable } from 'svelte/store';  export const isNavOpen = writable(false); ```  2. Update your root layout (`+layout.svelte`) to use the `isNavOpen` storen ```html <!-- src/routes/__layout.svelte --> <script>   import { isNavOpen } from '../store.js';    function toggleNav() {     isNavOpen.update(state => !state);   } </script>  {#if $isNavOpen}   <!-- Your navigation component here --> {/if}  <slot /> ```  3. Update your pages (`+page.svelte`) to use the `isNavOpen` store and toggle the navigationn ```html <!-- src/routes/+page.svelte --> <script>   import { isNavOpen } from '../store.js';    function toggleNav() {     isNavOpen.update(state => !state);   } </script>  <button on:click={toggleNav}>   Toggle Navigation </button>  <!-- Rest of the page content --> ```  Now, when you click the `Toggle Navigation` button on any page, it will update the `isNavOpen` store, and the root layout will respond accordingly, showing or hiding the navigation based on the store's value."
