							"To implement this functionality in SvelteKit, you can use the `touchstart`, `touchmove`, and `touchend` events to detect swipes and the `$app/stores` module to navigate between pages. Here's an example of how to achieve thisn 1. Install `svelte-swipe` package to handle swipe eventsn ```bash npm install svelte-swipe ```  2. Create a `_layout.svelte` file in the `/aryavarta/chapter/01` folder, which will wrap all the `[id].svelte` components, and add the following coden ```html <!-- /aryavarta/chapter/01/_layout.svelte --> <script>   import { onMount } from 'svelte';   import { goto } from '$app/navigation';   import { browser } from '$app/env';   import { Swipe } from 'svelte-swipe';    let currentPage = parseInt($page.params.id);    const navigate = (direction) => {     const nextPage = currentPage + direction;      // Update this condition if you have a specific number of pages     if (nextPage > 0) {       goto(`/aryavarta/chapter/01/${nextPage.toString().padStart(2, '0')}`);     }   };    const handleSwipe = (e) => {     if (e.detail.direction === 'left') {       navigate(1);     } else if (e.detail.direction === 'right') {       navigate(-1);     }   };    onMount(() => {     if (browser) {       import('svelte-swipe').then(({ Swipe }) => {         new Swipe(document.body, { threshold: 100 }).on('swipe', handleSwipe);       });     }  "
