							'Yes, there is a difference between naming it `_layout.svelte` and `+layout.svelte`.  SvelteKit uses a file-based routing system, and the naming conventions for layout components are as followsn - `_layout.svelte`: This is a normal layout component. It is used to wrap all the other components in the same folder and its nested folders. When a route is matched, the normal layout will be used to wrap the component associated with that route.  - `__layout.svelte`: This is a reset layout component. It is used to wrap all the other components in the same folder, but it does not inherit from any parent layouts. This is useful when you want to have a completely different layout for a specific folder without inheriting styles or behaviors from parent layouts.  There is no special behavior associated with the `+layout.svelte` naming convention. If you name your layout component `+layout.svelte`, it will be treated as a regular component and will not provide any layout functionality.'
