							"Yes, it is possible to use Prism.js to render code snippets within a text input area, but it would require some customization to achieve that.  By default, Prism.js is designed to highlight and format code snippets that are enclosed within HTML tags. However, you could use JavaScript to listen for changes to the text input area and apply Prism.js formatting to the text content.  One way to accomplish this is to use a JavaScript library like `prismjs` or `highlight.js` to apply syntax highlighting to the code snippets, and then update the content of the text input area with the formatted HTML.  Here's an example implementation using `prismjs`n 1. First, include the `prism.js` and `prism.css` files in your SvelteKit project.  2. Create a text input area in your Svelte componentn ``` <textarea bind:value={codeSnippet}></textarea> ```  3. Use `prismjs` to format the content of the text input area when the value of `codeSnippet` changesn ``` <script>   import Prism from 'prismjs';   import 'prismjs/themes/prism.css';      let codeSnippet = '';    function formatCodeSnippet() {     const formattedCode = Prism.highlight(codeSnippet, Prism.languages.javascript, 'javascript');     const textarea = document.querySelector('textarea');     textarea.innerHTML = formattedCode;   }    $: formatCodeSnippet(); </script> ```  In this example, `Prism.highlight()` is used to format the code snippet in JavaScript syntax, and the formatted code is then set as the innerHTML of the textarea element.  Note that this is just a simple example and may require further customization depending on your specific requirements."
