							"You can use the command-line tool `sfnt2woff` to convert TTF fonts into WOFF and WOFF2 formats on macOS. Here are the stepsn 1. Open the Terminal app on your macOS computer. 2. Install `sfnt2woff` if you haven't already by running the command `brew install woff2`. 3. Navigate to the directory where your TTF font file is located using the `cd` command. 4. To convert the TTF file into WOFF format, run the command `sfnt2woff <fontname>.ttf`. This will create a new file with the same name as the TTF file, but with the extension `.woff`. 5. To convert the TTF file into WOFF2 format, run the command `woff2_compress <fontname>.ttf`. This will create a new file with the same name as the TTF file, but with the extension `.woff2`.  That's it! You should now have both WOFF and WOFF2 versions of your TTF font file in the same directory."
