							"Supabase Auth helpers are a set of utility functions provided by Supabase to simplify common authentication tasks in web applications. These helpers are built on top of the Supabase Auth API and provide a more convenient way to perform common tasks such as signing up new users, logging in existing users, and managing user sessions.  Some of the Supabase Auth helpers includen 1. `signUp()`: This method allows you to create a new user account with a specified email and password.  2. `signIn()`: This method allows you to authenticate a user with their email and password.  3. `signOut()`: This method allows you to sign out the currently authenticated user.  4. `user()`: This method returns the current authenticated user's information, including their email, ID, and other details.  5. `session()`: This method returns information about the current user session, including the access token and the session expiry time.  6. `onAuthStateChange()`: This method allows you to subscribe to changes in the user authentication state, such as when a user signs in or signs out.  By using these helpers, you can simplify your authentication logic and reduce the amount of boilerplate code you need to write to manage user authentication and sessions."
