						content_type: 'text',
						parts: [
							"  There are several free tools available for documenting a website's design system. Here are a few optionsn 1. Google Docs/Google Sheets: Google Docs and Sheets are free and easy-to-use tools for documenting your design system. You can create a table of contents to organize your documentation, add images and screenshots to illustrate your design elements, and collaborate with your team members in real-time.  2. Figma: Figma is a free design tool that allows you to create and share design systems with your team. You can create a design library to store all your design elements, add annotations and notes to your design components, and export your design system as a style guide.  3. Notion: Notion is a powerful note-taking and collaboration tool that can be used to document your design system. You can create a table of contents, add pages for each section of your design system, and embed images and videos to illustrate your design elements.  4. GitHub: GitHub is a code repository tool that can also be used to document your design system. You can create a repository for your design system, use Markdown to format your documentation, and version control your design system.  5. InVision Design System Manager: InVision DSM is a free tool that allows you to create and manage your design system. You can create a design library, add annotations and notes to your design elements, and export your design system as a style guide.  Ultimately, the best tool for documenting your website's design system will depend on your specific needs and preferences. It's important to choose a tool that is easy to use, collaborative, and allows you to organize and present your design system effectively."
						]
